        "timestamp": "2020-09-23 06:50:21.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2\n\nJust looked into other projects' \"setup.sh\" scripts and retagging seems a common pattern with a slight difference that the images get retagged to \"latest\" tag there and relevant docker-compose files use images with \"latest\" tag instead of an image tag taken from env var and exported in setup.sh.\n\nThere could be some uniformity in those scripts but seems like each project has it's own \"way\" here.",
